  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>The project Engineer for the Building Management System (IBMS/BMS), Security System and Extra Low Voltage System (ELV)</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Assist in reviewing sales handover budget to ensure that it complies with the company policies, statutory requirements and contract specifications</li>\n  <li>To plan and develop the project schedules in compliance with customer requirements, deadlines, and/or milestones. To track the project progression in the field and update the schedules regularly to ensure that the activities are progressing within the scheduled timelines.</li>\n  <li>Liaise with consultants, architects, main contractors and subcontractors for technical matters and job execution.</li>\n  <li>Attending site meetings and coordinating with stakeholders, customers, architects, consultants, and planning the related activities for the assigned projects.</li>\n  <li>Prepare and design shop drawings,document submission and site supervision.</li>\n  <li>Plan and monitor the FAT, testing &amp; commissioning, and inspection activities within the project scheduled timelines.</li>\n  <li>Sourcing and negotiating the material/sub-Contractor procurement within budget</li>\n  <li>Ensure timely completion of the assigned tasks, particularly for the handover schedules.</li>\n  <li>Preparing the quotation for the variation order works.</li>\n  <li>As and when to take on new assignments.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>At least a Diploma or Degree in engineering studies.</li>\n  <li>Minimum 2 years of working experience in relevant fields.</li>\n  <li>Knowledge in DDC, PLC, HVAC, Card Access, CCTV, Fire Alarm, PA/BGM and ELV, Structure Cabling &amp; etc.</li>\n  <li>Familiar with BIM (Navisworks) and/or AutoCAD.</li>\n  <li>Entry-level candidates who are interested in project management are also welcome to apply.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>What we offer:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Flexible Work Arrangement (FWA): Work from Home and Flexible Working Hours</li>\n  <li>Working Day: Monday to Friday (5-day week)</li>\n  <li>Annual Wage Supplement (AWS) or Completion bonus</li>\n  <li>Performance bonus/Variable bonus.</li>\n  <li>Comprehensive Medical Benefits and Insurance coverage.</li>\n  <li>The company provides shuttle bus services with pick-up and drop-off points at Admiralty and Sengkang MRT stations.</li>\n</ul>",
